      <td width="81%" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"> 
        <div align="center"> 
		<p align="center"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Comic Sans MS" size="2"><b><font size="3" color="#000000">
		LDSG Workshop on "Symbolic Dynamics and Number Theory in Statistical Mechanics"</font></b></font></p>
          <p align="left"><font color="#000000" face="Comic Sans MS" size="2">You 
		  are invited to attend an afternoon meeting on "Symbolic Dynamics and Number Theory in Statistical Mechanics", 
		  to be held at Queen Mary, University of London, 24 February 2006.</font></p>
	  <p align="left"><font color="#000000" face="Comic Sans MS" size="2">
		  Invited Speakers:<br>
		  Stefano Isola (Università di Camerino)<br>
	    Peter Kleban (University of Maine)<br>
	    Dieter Mayer (Technische Universität Clausthal)<br>
	    Anatoly Zhigljavsky (Cardiff University)
            </font></p>
	  <p align="left"><font color="#000000" face="Comic Sans MS" size="2">
	    All are welcome, and we can provide some financial support for students
	    to attend. Students wanting to claim support should bring travel receipts.
		 </font></p>
    <hr>
          <p align="center"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Comic Sans MS" size="2"><b><font size="3" color="#000000"> Programme</font></b></font>
           </font></p>
	  <p align="left"><font color="#000000" face="Comic Sans MS" size="2">
		  1:30-2:20 Stefano Isola "Maps, spectra and trees" <a href="isola.pdf">abstract</a> <a href="isolaslides.pdf">slides</a><br>
		  2:30-3:20 Peter Kleban "The Farey Fraction Spin Chain" <a href="kleban.html">abstract</a> <a href="klebanslides.pdf">slides</a><br>
                  - Refreshments - <br>
		  4:00-4:50 Dieter Mayer "The transfer operator of Rosen´s lambda expansion and period functions for the Hecke triangle groups" <a href="mayer.pdf">abstract</a> <a href="mayer/mayer.html">slides</a><br>
		  5:00-5:50 Anatoly Zhigljavsky "Partitions of the unit interval generated by the Farey points" <a href="zhigljavsky.pdf">abstract</a><br>
	  <p align="left"><font color="#000000" face="Comic Sans MS" size="2">
		  All talks will take place in the Mathematics Lecture Theatre. Refreshments will be served in the Mathematics Common Room.</font></p>

          <p align="left"><font color="#000000" face="Comic Sans MS" size="2">Contact: 
		  <a href="http://www.maths.qmul.ac.uk/~tp">Thomas Prellberg</a>, 
		  School of Mathematical Sciences, Queen Mary, University of London 
		 </font></p>
